# Localhost / dev server ‚Äî repeat this process every time

This repo is **Express + Vite on one port** (default **3000**, or next free port). It is **not** Create React App on :3000 with a separate API on :5000 unless the user is in a different project.

When the user reports **localhost not working**, **connection refused**, **site can‚Äôt be reached**, **blank page**, or **dev won‚Äôt start**, **execute** (yourself, in the project root):

1. **`npm run dev:doctor`** ‚Äî prints Node/tsx/port/script checks and the exact URLs to use.
2. **`npm run dev`** ‚Äî capture the **first** error. If the shell has no `tsx`/`npx` on PATH, `package.json` must use **`node ./node_modules/tsx/dist/cli.mjs watch server/_core/index.ts`** (not bare `tsx`).
3. **Blank UI but `__vop_ping` returns ok** ‚Äî often **`NODE_ENV=production`** in `.env` while Vite is skipped. **`server/_core/loadEnv.ts`** must force `NODE_ENV=development` when **`npm_lifecycle_event === "dev"`** OR when argv shows **any** `tsx` run of **`server/_core/index`** (with **or without** `watch`). **Do not** narrow this back to watch-only ‚Äî IDE ‚ÄúRun‚Äù and one-shot `tsx server/_core/index.ts` would stay production and look ‚Äúbroken‚Äù. Regression coverage: **`server/_core/loadEnv.test.ts`** ‚Üí **`vopDevServerArgv.ts`** (`isTsxVopServerEntryFromArgv`).
4. **Esbuild / TransformError in `shared/knoxKnowledge.ts`** ‚Äî the string `KNOX_KNOWLEDGE_BASE_SANITIZED` is a template literal; any markdown **code** backticks inside it must be **escaped** as `` \` `` or the server never starts.
5. **Port busy** ‚Äî log says ‚Äúusing port 3001‚Äù; or free **3000** (Windows: `netstat -ano | findstr :3000` then `taskkill /PID ‚Ä¶ /F`).
6. **Verify** ‚Äî open **`http://127.0.0.1:<port>/__vop_ping`** ‚Äî response must be plain **`ok`**. If not, nothing is listening on that port.
7. **Do not** tell the user to rely on **`http://localhost:5173/`** alone for this app ‚Äî Vite middleware shares the Express port; `scripts/dev-hint.mjs` explains this.
8. **`server/routers/github.ts`** ‚Äî `gh auth token` must not use bash-only `2>/dev/null`; use `stdio: ['ignore','pipe','ignore']` on Windows.
9. **Touch handlers** ‚Äî never destructure **`end: e`** (or any binding named **`e`**) in the same block as a parameter **`e: React.TouchEvent`**; it causes TDZ / `ReferenceError` on **`e.touches`** (see fix in `ZoomableChart.tsx`).

After fixes, **`npm run dev`** again and confirm **`__vop_ping`** before closing the task.

## Proactive ‚Äî debug before it happens

- After editing **`shared/knoxKnowledge.ts`** inside **`KNOX_KNOWLEDGE_BASE_SANITIZED`**: run **`npm run dev`** once ‚Äî unescaped markdown code backticks inside that template literal kill startup (esbuild ‚ÄúExpected ';'‚Äù / similar).
- Before merging changes to **`package.json` `dev`**, **`server/_core/index.ts`**, **`server/_core/vite.ts`**, or **`vite.config.ts`**: run **`npm run dev:doctor`** then a short **`npm run dev`** smoke test and hit **`/__vop_ping`**.
- **Retention:** this file is the project‚Äôs retained ‚Äúmemory‚Äù for localhost. For a personal Cursor reminder across repos, save a short note in **Cursor Settings ‚Üí Rules / Memories** pointing at **`npm run dev:doctor`** + **`__vop_ping`** for V-OP.
